content.description: Clip the first 2 bolts then head left out into slightly steeper terrain, eventually traversing right and joining "Freestyle" on the last 2 bolts. Fun and pumpy warm up! Â  Shared Anchors are 2 Cold Shuts.
content.location: Left most line on the wall, shares first 2 bolts with all 3 climbs, shares last 2 bolts with middle line.

content.description:
Start on the first 2 shared bolts, then head right up the ramp. Optional protection for the spicy exposed ramp would be to clip a long runner on bolt #3 of Freestyle, drag is not bad. Head right and up through slightly overhanging terrain, climbing over a spooky hollow section then take it to the chains through varied terrain. A bit taller than the rest, and just as fun!

Watch for crunchy rock on this one. This wall doesn't see a lot of traffic, which it could use.
content.protection: 12 bolts, 1 optional runner, cold shut anchors.
content.location: Rightmost and tallest line up the wall through black streaks.

content.description: Middle line on the wall, heading into the left facing and beautiful layback / flake white section. Pull on thin and overhung holds through the crux and join Ultimate Frisbee on the last 2 bolts. Very Fun !
content.location: Middle route on wall. Most direct line.
